result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Willie Davis in court, in custody.  Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court for Willie Davis.  Attorney Annie Louk in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for return on doctors report.  Parties review and do not contest the findings of Dr. Ana Garcia dated 9/22/2022.  Court finds the defendant is incompetent to proceed at this time but is likely to become competent.  Court orders proceedings suspended.   Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame.   Case adjourned to Br. 9 for Review hearing on doctor's report.
Review hearing scheduled for January 6, 2023 at 11:00 am.

Pursuant to letter received from DHS, the competency evaluation will not be completed prior to next scheduled hearing date of 9/15/2022.  With Court approval, and approval from the parties, the hearing on Doctor's Report Return is rescheduled to 10/7/2022 at 10:30 am.

Defendant Willie Davis in court, in custody.  Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court for Willie Davis.  Attorney Patrick T. Franken in court for Annie Louk for the State of Wisconsin. 

Matter following lower Case 21CF4515 for Doctor's Report Return. Doctor Collins report received and filed.  Court orders defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to be transported FORTHWITH to a DHS facility for an inpatient competency re-evaluation. Case adjourned to Br. 9. Doctor's Report Return scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Deputy Ndina on the court record to advise court of Governor's warrant issued July 2022 is good for one year.

Defendant Willie Davis in court with attorney Heather L. Johnson.  Defendant Willie Davis in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Willie Davis appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant has lower number case 21CF4515 pending.  Defendant is advised this case is reassigned to Judge Van Grunsven, Branch 09 to follow lower pending case. Court suspended proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT.  Status conference scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
